    "created_at": "2016-05-31T22:21:45Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-05-31T22:24:13Z",
    "body": "I suspect I am running into the same issue here. openSUSE 13.1 (64-bits), XFCE4. My [application](https://git.cryto.net/joepie91/npmbar) is bound to a hotkey (F8), and is visibility-toggled when that hotkey is pressed, and [focused immediately afterwards](https://git.cryto.net/joepie91/npmbar/src/a94e22b926e14983d96aac411e09016a07c53a1d/src/app.js#L44-L47).\n\nThe following **works**:\n1. Start application\n2. Hit F8 to show\n3. Enter search query\n4. Hit F8 to hide\n5. Hit F8 to show\n6. Modify search query\n\nThe following **does not work**:\n1. Start application\n2. Hit F8 to show\n3. Enter search query\n4. Hit F8 to hide\n5. **Type something into the previously focused window, which automatically regains focus (eg. my editor)**\n6. Hit F8 to show _(fails to focus, even though the window is shown correctly)_\n7. Modify search query _(output goes to editor, not my Electron application)_\n\nIt's unclear to me whether this is a result of desktop environment settings, but other applications like Guake (which uses a similar visibility-toggle mechanism) do not have this issue at all.\n"
